NO BALL! Oh, dear! That slipped out of his hand probably! Embuldeniya bangs it into the deck and the ball bounces a couple of times before reaching the batter. Hope stays back and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out.
Another ball, fuller in length, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it watchfully.
FOUR! Punished by Brathwaite! Shorter in length, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite rocks back and pulls it in front of square to collect a boundary.
FOUR! STREAKY! Flatter ball, coming in with the angle from off. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to play across the line but gets a thick inside edge and it runs past the keeper to go into the fine leg fence.
Tossed up, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite keeps it out.
Nicely tossed up, on a length, around leg. Kraigg Brathwaite tucks it to the leg side with soft hands.
Short and on middle, kept out.
Flatter and around leg, Shai Hope shuffles and misses his tuck to get hit on the pad. A loud appeal for LBW but looked like it would slide down the leg side.
Flatter and on off, SH blocks it out.
Short again, pushed away to the leg side.

Again, Ramesh Mendis keeps the length short and serves it around leg, Shai Hope goes back, getting stuck on his crease, as he looked to tuck but misses and gets hit above the pad. An excited appeal again for LBW but turned down.
Short again, on off and middle, the ball lands and spins in, Shai Hope looks to flick but gets hit high on the pad. Hope is struggling to read the spin of Mendis here.
Fuller in length, around middle. Kraigg Brathwaite prods and eases it down to mid on.
Short ball, just outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite backs away and cuts it to deep cover for a single.
Tossed up, around off. Shai Hope presses forward to block it.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Shai Hope gets behind the line of the ball to keep it out.
Floated, on a length, around middle. Shai Hope defends it solidly.
Nicely tossed up, around off. Hope clears his front leg and drives it to wide of mid off for a single. Suranga Lakmal does well at mid off to keep it to one by moving across quickly to his left.
Flatter ball, turning down leg. Shai Hope tucks it to the leg side.
Tossed up, around middle. Shai Hope pushes it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball, on a length, around middle. Shai Hope defends it off the front foot.
Flatter ball, spinning in from middle. Shai Hope blocks it out.
A half-tracker, around middle. Shai Hope goes back in his crease and pulls it along the ground towards deep mid-wicket. A single taken!
Tossed up, around middle. Kraigg Brathwaite drags it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, around off. Shai Hope blocks it off the front foot.
Turn and bounce! Tossed up, on a length, outside off, spinning away sharply. Shai Hope stays back to defend but the ball spins and bounces past his outside edge.
Floated, around off. Shai Hope blocks it out.
Fuller in length, outside off. Shai Hope defends it to the off side.
Overpitched ball, on leg. Shai Hope clips it to wide of mid on and scampers through for a single.
Tossed up, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite prods to defend this one out.
Floated, around off, turning in late. Shai Hope nudges it to square leg.
Tossed up, around off. Shai Hope keeps it out watchfully.
Loopy ball, around middle and leg. Shai Hope flicks hard but it hits the short leg fielder.
Well bowled! Nicely tossed up, around middle and leg, spinning in sharply. Shai Hope looks to defend but it goes off the thick inside edge past the short leg fielder.
Tossed up delivery, on off. Shai Hope blocks it.
Floated, on a length, around off. Shai Hope is solid in his defence.
Slightly short, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite rocks back and eases it to mid off for a single.
Tossed up, just outside off. Shai Hope prods to defend this one.
FOUR! Shai Hope breaks the shackles! A welcome boundary for West Indies! Loopy ball, on a length, around off. Hope lofts it over mid off and the ball races away to the fence.
Flatter ball, outside off, turning away sharply. Shai Hope sits back and sways away from the line of the ball.
Flatter and quicker, on middle. Shai Hope tucks it to the leg side.
This is darted on the pads. Shai Hope hangs back and nudges it to wide of mid-wicket for a run.
Huge appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested! Floated, around middle and spinning in a bit. Hope stays back to defend but he misses and gets hit high on his pad.
Floated, around middle. Shai Hope blocks it out.
Tossed up, on a length, around middle. Shai Hope keeps it out.
Fuller in length, on middle. Shai Hope skips down and eases it to mid on.
Another appeal for LBW but this one was going down leg! Flatter ball, around middle and turning down leg. Shai Hope looks to flick but misses and gets rapped on his pad.
Floated, around off. Shai Hope defends it off the front foot.
Nicely tossed up, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it solidly.
Another ball, fuller in length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite presses forward and keeps it out.
Flatter ball, darted down leg. Kraigg Brathwaite sits back and tucks it to short fine leg.
Loopy ball, around leg. Kraigg Brathwaite squeezes it out back to the bowler.

OUT! BOWLED! That is a peach of a  delivery to get rid of West Indies' skipper! Change of angle has done the trick for the left-arm spinner! Embuldeniya tosses it up, around leg. Brathwaite lunges forward to block it but he gets deceived by the turn and flight and misses it. The ball just clips the bail and Sri Lankan players are over the moon! Huge wicket this for the hosts and their bowlers have toiled hard for it! Braithwaite's impressive knock comes to an end as he walks back to the hut quite dejected.
Tossed up, around off. Roston Chase defends it off the front foot.
Short and on the body, nudged to the leg side.
On middle, Hope plays this through mid on and rotates the strike.
On middle again, dragged to short mid-wicket.
Roston Chase pulls this short ball through square leg and opens his account here.
Around off, Shai Hope pulls this one straight into the short leg's body. Oshada Fernando was the fielder there and he would have felt that hard.
On off, blocked.
Floated on off, kept out.
An action replay of the previous delivery.
On off and middle, gently kept out.

FOUR! Tossed up, on middle, Roston Chase gets low and sweeps this one over the square leg fielder. Pathum Nissanka chases after this, dives ahead, but the ball lands ahead of him and goes to the ropes. No ball called as Lasith Embuldeniya oversteps his mark again.
On off, pushed to covers.
Loopy, on off, blocked.

Lasith could not hold on! On middle, fuller, Roston Chase makes some room and slaps this one back to the right of Lasith Embuldeniya, who dives that side, but the ball brushes his fingers and goes away. That was hit very hard and would have been hard to keep a hold off!
On middle, blocked.
Tossed up, on off, Hope skips down and dabs it back to the bowler.
Flighted around off, Shai blocks.
On middle, Shai Hope works this through mid-wicket for one.
Flatter, on the pads, worked through square leg.
Full on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up, on off, Hope keeps it out.
Flatter, outside off, Shai Hope pushes this to the off side.
Around off, pushed to covers again.
Flighted on off, Shai Hope presses forward and blocks.
Fuller, on middle, again, a solid defense from Hope.
Shai dabs this fuller ball back onto the deck.
Short and spinning in, around off, pushed down to mid on.
Given a nice loop, around off, Chase blocks it well.
FOUR! Very well played. Solid stroke. That will give Chase some confidence. Fuller, outside off, Roston Chase gets to the pitch of the ball and smoothly drives this through covers. Boundary.
On middle, flicked to the leg side.
Again, Chase goes back and his flick is found by the square leg fielder.
Quicker on the pads, Roston gets his bat down and defends it out.
Loopy this time, outside off, Hope shuffles and then defends it to the off side.
Lasith Embuldeniya drags his length back and serves it short and outside off, Hope camps back and slashes but only finds the point fielder.

Well bowled by Lasith! Gives it air, lands it fuller around off, the ball lands, turns away, bounces slightly more too, as Shai Hope misses his attempted defense and the ball whiskers past the outside edge to Dinesh Chandimal.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
On off, kept out.
Again, some nice bit of flight, on off, Hope is solid in his defense. West Indies now trail by just 26 runs.
Praveen Jayawickrama starts his new spell with a fuller ball on the pads, Chase goes back and jams this one out.
Fuller again, on middle and off, Roston digs it out to covers.
The length is consistently fuller, outside off, Roston Chase punches this, but only manages to hit the silly point fielder. Oshada Fernando was the man present there.
On middle, hit to covers.
Misfield and a run! On middle, fuller again, Roston Chase pushes this to covers, where the fielder only half-stops this, which allows the batters to take the run.
Around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up, around off. Roston Chase blocks it out.
Floated, on a length, around off. Roston Chase keeps it out.
Loopy ball, outside off. Roston Chase drives hard but straight to the cover fielder.
Tossed up, around off. Roston Chase presses forward and defends it to cover-point.
Fuller in length, around off. Roston Chase lunges forward to block this one.
Overpitched ball, around off. Roston Chase digs it out towards mid off.
Flatter ball, turning down leg. Shai Hope nudges it to the leg side for an easy single.
Flatter ball, around off. Roston Chase stays back and punches it to mid on.
Tossed up, around off. Roston Chase blocks it out.
Floated, around middle and spinning in sharply. Roston Chase misses his flick and gets hit high on his pad.

OUT! TAKEN! Ramesh Mendis strikes yet again and West Indies lose their fourth wicket now! The ploy of attacking the pads has worked for Mendis and the Lankans are delighted! Flatter ball, around leg, and spinning in late. Chase looks to work it on the leg side but it goes off the inner half of the blade towards leg slip where Pathum Nissanka takes a sharp catch.
Howout: c Charith Asalanka b Ramesh Mendis

Commentary: Just short of the fielder! Tossed up, outside off. Kyle Mayers looks to drive but it goes off the outer half towards the cover-point fielder. The fielder there dives in front but the ball falls short of him.
Flatter and quicker, around middle. Shai Hope turns it to wide of mid-wicket for a run.
On a length, around leg. Kyle Mayers blocks it out.
Tossed up, on a length, around middle. Kyle Mayers looks to defend but he gets an inside edge onto his pad.
An appeal for LBW but the umpire says no. Floated, around middle and turning in. Kyle Mayers looks to defend but he misses and gets hit high on his pad.
Tossed up, around off. Mayers blocks it off the front foot.
BEATEN! What a delivery! Flatter ball, around off, going on with the angle. Kyle Mayers plays for the turn as he prods to defend but the ball zips past his outside edge.
Flatter and quicker, around middle. Shai Hope eases it to mid on for a single.
Flatter ball, on off. Kyle Mayers blocks it out.
Nicely tossed up, on middle. Kyle Mayers looks to defend but it goes off the thick inside edge towards square leg.

NOT OUT! Flatter ball, around middle, going on with the angle. Kyle Mayers looks to block but he misses and gets rapped on his pad. Ramesh Mendis appeals but the umpire says no. Dimuth Karunaratne opts for a review but the Ball Tracker suggests that it would have been umpire's call on the wickets and so, the on-field decision stays.
Tossed up, on off. Kyle Mayers pushes it back to the bowler. Ramesh Mendis collects the ball and has a shy at the keeper. Kyle Mayers doesn't leave his crease and he tucks the ball on the leg side.
Tossed up, on off. Kyle Mayers keeps it out.
Floated, around off. Shai Hope defends it.
Flatter ball, darted on the pads. Shai Hope looks to defend but he misses and gets hit high on his pad.
In the air...but safe! Loopy ball, around off. Shai Hope looks to sweep but gets a top edge which falls over the mid on fielder. The batters take a couple.
FOUR! Punished by Hope! Shorter in length, down leg. Shai Hope gets back in his crease and pulls it behind square on the leg side for a boundary.
Flatter ball, on middle. Shai Hope tucks it to the leg side for one.
On a length, around middle and leg. Kyle Mayers nudges it behind square on the leg side for a couple of runs.
Flatter ball, turning way down leg. Shai Hope lets it be.
Tossed up, around off. Shai Hope blocks it out.

OUT! LBW! Ramesh Mendis is on a roll and he gets his man this time! Looped up, around off, spinning in sharply. Shai Hope lunges forward to block but the ball sneaks through and hits him on the front pad. Ramesh Mendis appeals and the umpire raises his finger. Shai Hope consults for a review with his partner but they decide to go against it and Hope walks back.
Nicely tossed up, around off. Holder presse forward to defend but gets a thick inside edge which falls just wide of the short leg fielder.
Tossed up, well outside off. Jason Holder reaches out and works it to point.
Fuller in length, around middle. Jason Holder prods and flicks it to mid-wicket. A wicket-maiden from Mendis!
Loopy, on off, kept out.
Short and on middle, flicked off the back foot towards mid-wicket, who half-stops this. One run.
Given a nice loop, around off, gently pushed back to Praveen by Holder.
Darted around off and middle, Jason blocks well again.

NOT OUT! The review does not send Holder back! Praveen serves this fuller, around off, Holder steps forward, looking to block, but misses his attempt and gets pinged on the pad. A very enthusiastic appeal for LBW by the Lankans but the umpire stays still. There is a discussion regarding whether they should take the review and the hosts go for it this time. UltraEdge shows that there was no bat involved. Ball Tracker shows that the ball was missing the leg pole due to the angle. Sri Lanka lose their final review and Holder survives.
Outside off, dabbed to point.
Angled around off, well kept out.
Tosses this one up, fuller outside off, Kyle Mayers presses ahead and looks to block, but the ball takes the outer half and dribbles through gully, for one.
Slightly short, outside off, spins in, JH gets ahead and defends to point.
FOUR! Lovely shot from Holder and now Windies are just 7 runs behind! Loopy, fuller, outside off, Jason Holder creams this one through covers. No point chasing after that. Boundary for Holder!

OUT! LBW! Ramesh Mendis gets yet another one and the Lankans are using the new cherry to good effect! Holder is not able to hang around for long and the Windies lose their sixth. Mendis serves this flatter and around off and middle, spins in slightly, as Holder goes on the back foot and looks to whip it to the leg side but misses and gets hit slightly high on the pad. An appeal but the umpire agrees with the Lankans and raises his finger. Holder goes for the review right away. Looks like he thinks that the height could be an issue. No bat on this. Ball Tracker shows that the wickets would be umpire's call. So, even though Jason Holder has to go back, they do not lose the review.

OUT! BOWLED 'EM! Ramesh Mendis is unstoppable right now. A golden duck for Joshua Da Silva and the West Indies are in some trouble now. A 5-fer for Mendis and he is running the show. Da Silva gets deceived on this occasion. Mendis serves this one fuller, loops it up nicely too and it is bowled outside off, Joshua Da Silva looks to pat the ball down, but the ball spins in this time and misses his blade. Goes on to clip the top of the off pole and the Lankans are all pumped up. Mendis will be on a hat-trick in his next over!
Tossed up, around off. Kyle Mayers pushes it back to the bowler.
Overpitched ball, around middle. Kyle Mayers drags it to long on and takes a single.
Flatter ball, around off. Kemar Roach prods to block this one out.
Fuller in length, around middle and spinning away late. Kemar Roach waist for the ball to turn and defends it.
Tossed up, on a length, around middle. Kemar Roach looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pad.
FOUR! West Indies are now behind by 2 runs! Fuller, sliding down the leg pole, Kemar Roach gets low and sweeps this one past the keeper and into the fine leg fence.
No hat-trick for Ramesh Mendis for now! Fuller, on off, well blocked out by Mayers.
Outside off, shorter, Kyle Mayers goes back and slaps this to the right of the backward point fielder, for a single.
FOUR! West Indies now ahead by 3 runs! A good stroke. Outside off, fuller in length, Kemar Roach leans and sweetly times this through covers. Boundary.
Flatter, on off, kept out.

Was there an edge there? Oh yes, there was! Should have been the sixth wicket for Mendis! Shortish this time, outside off, Kemar Roach looks to defend but misses this time and the ball kisses the outside edge and goes to the keeper, where Dinesh Chandimal drops this one.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Shortish outside off, guided through backward point for a single.

OUT! TAKEN! That's an easy catch and the 8th one departs. Praveen Jayawickrama bowls this really well, it is served around off, fuller too, the ball lands and there is just a hint of away turn, which is enough, as Kemar Roach presses forward, looking to defend, but the ball catches the outside edge and goes to first slip, where Dhananjaya de Silva makes no mistake. West Indies in front by just 4 runs right now!
Howout: c Dhananjaya de Silva b Praveen Jayawickrama

Commentary: Down the leg side, Veerasammy Permaul misses the flick.
Floated, around off, kept out.
Flatter, outside off, punched to covers now.
Outside off, fuller, pushed to the silly point fielder.
Around middle and leg, fuller, Kyle Mayers looks to hit it to the leg side but misses and gets hit on the pad. A loud appeal for LBW but nothing doing says the umpire.
On middle, hit down towards long on for a couple of runs.
Short and on middle, knocked through mid on for a run.
Flatter, on off, defended to the leg side.
Short again, Permaul blocks it to the leg side.
Tosses this one up, fuller outside off, pushed away to the off side.
Shortish, around off, pushed back to the bowler.
On middle and leg, turning in, Mayers misses his tuck and gets hit on the pad.
Short and on leg, pulled through square leg for one.

That should have been held! Looks like Ramesh Mendis is the culprit! Given a nice bit of loop, outside off, fuller, Veerasammy Permaul makes room and slaps this to covers, where Ramesh Mendis dives to his right, but is not able to hold on. One run.

FOUR! Bounces just ahead of Ramesh Mendis again. Fuller, on middle, Kyle Mayers drags this one hard towards deep mid-wicket. Ramesh Mendis runs ahead, misjudges this one slightly, as the ball bounces ahead of him and runs away to the ropes.
Pushed to the off side for a single.
Short outside off, slapped through covers for one.
Short, around off, hooked through mid-wicket for a brace.
On off, blocked.
A full toss on off, hit to mid off.
On the pads, nudged to square leg.
Flat and on the pads, worked to deep mid-wicket for one.
Full and around off, VP skips down and slams this to mid off.
On middle, VP heaves this one to mid on this time.
Short and on off, well kept out.
Full on middle, Veerasammy Permaul gets low and slog-sweeps this to deep square leg where Ramesh Mendis runs to his left and stops the ball. One.
On middle, Kyle Mayers drags this one in between deep mid-wicket and deep square leg for one.
Tossed up, around off, pushed to mid off for one.
Starts with a shortish ball on off and middle, kept out by Permaul.
Darted on middle, Veerasammy Permaul slams this one to the right of mid-wicket, who misfields, allowing the batters to take one.
Outside off, dabbed to point.
On middle, kept out.
SIX! That is a brilliant shot. That went miles in the air! Fuller, tossed up, outside off, Kyle Mayers gets low and mows a slog-sweep and whacks this over deep mid-wicket!
On middle and leg, knocked down to long on for one.
On middle, worked to the leg side.
Flat, on off, punched through covers for one.
Shorter, on middle and leg, Veerasammy Permaul knocks this behind square leg for one.
On off, blocked.
On middle, fuller, pushed back to Lasith.
On middle, knocked to the leg side. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 3!
Flatter ball, darted on the pads. Veerasammy Permaul keeps it out.
Overpitched ball, on middle. Veerasammy Permaul digs it out to long on for a run.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Kyle Mayers stays back and punches it to deep cover for a single.
Floated, around middle. Veerasammy Permaul gets behind the line of the ball to defend.
Tossed up, around leg. Veerasammy Permaul misses his flick and the ball brushes his thigh pad before going to the leg slip fielder.
Flatter ball, shorter in length, on middle. Veerasammy Permaul gets back in his crease and tucks it to deep square leg for one.
Tossed up, on a length, around off. Veerasammy Permaul blocks it out.
A bit quicker, around off. Veerasammy Permaul hangs back to block this one.
Loopy ball, outside off. Veerasammy Permaul drills it back to the bowler.
Flatter ball, coming in with the angle from off. Veerasammy Permaul works it to cover-point.
Too full, around middle. Veerasammy Permaul clears his front leg and pushes it back to the bowler.
On a length, around off. Veerasammy Permaul presses forward to keep it out.
Flatter ball, around off. Kyle Mayers pushes it back to the bowler.
Fuller in length, way outside off. Kyle Mayers leaves it alone.
Fired in, around middle. Kyle Mayers rocks back and punches it to cover-point.
Tossed up, outside off. Kyle Mayers drives hard but straight to the cover fielder.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Kyle Mayers stays back and cuts it towards the deep point fielder to collect a single.
An appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested! Tossed up, on a length, around middle, spinning in sharply. Veerasammy Permaul misses his flick and gets hit high on his pad.
Flatter ball, down leg. Kyle Mayers bunts it behind square on the leg side for a run.
Tossed up, on a length, around middle. Veerasammy Permaul clips it to mid-wicket.
Fuller in length, on middle. Veerasammy Permaul presses forward and works it to long on for a run.
Flatter ball, around off, going on with the angle. Kyle Mayers looks to block but it goes off the thick outside edge past the slip fielder. The batters cross for a run.
BEATEN! Floated, around off and spinning away sharply. Veerasammy Permaul looks to defend but the ball spins past his outside edge.
FOUR! Too short and outside off. Veerasammy Permaul rocks back and cuts it past the cover fielder to collect a boundary. West Indies lead by 42 runs now!
Flatter ball, around off. Kyle Mayers drives it to cover.
Tossed up, around middle. Kyle Mayers prods to block this one.
Flatter ball, on off. Kyle Mayers sits back and pushes it to cover.

NOT OUT! Nicely tossed up, around off, spinning away late. Kyle Mayers looks to slog but he misses as the ball spins past his blade. Dinesh Chandimal collects the ball cleanly behind the sticks and whips the bails off. The decision of stumping is sent upstairs but Mayers had his back foot grounded.
Tossed up, on off. Kyle Mayers blocks it out.
Fuller in length, outside off. Kyle Mayers pushes it back to the bowler. A maiden over from Mendis!

OUT! BOWLED! Lasith Embuldeniya gets the much-needed breakthrough for his side! He hurls a flatter ball, around off, that goes on with the angle. Veerasammy Permaul plays for the turn and looks to block but the ball sneaks through his bat and pad and rattles his middle stump. West Indies lose their ninth wicket now!
Flatter ball, around off. Jomel Warrican stays back and blocks it out.
Tossed up, around middle. Jomel Warrican prods to defend this one out.
Floated, down leg. Jomel Warrican gets back and glances it behind square on the leg side for a run to get off the mark.
Flatter ball, on leg. Kyle Mayers nudges it to square leg.
On the pads and Kyle Mayers tucks it past square leg to collect a single. He keeps the strike for the next over!
FOUR! BANG! Tossed up, in the slot, around off. Mayers powers it past the bowler and the ball races away to the long off fence. West Indies bring up their 250!
Flatter ball, outside off. Kyle Mayers sits back and works it to cover for one.
Tossed up, around middle. Jomel Warrican defends it off the front foot but the ball hits him high on his bat and it pops up just wide of the short leg fielder.
On a length, around off. Jomel Warrican blocks it out.
Floated, around off. Jomel Warrican keeps it out.
Flatter ball, spinning in sharply from middle. Jomel Warrican plays it with soft hands to the right of the short leg fielder.
Tossed up, around leg. Kyle Mayers skips down to heave it away but he misses and gets hit on his pad.
Flatter ball, turning down leg. Kyle Mayers looks to pull but he misses.
Fuller in length, outside off. Kyle Mayers looks to drive but it goes off the inner half towards the bowler.
Flatter ball, on the pads. Kyle Mayers tucks it to deep mid-wicket bit does not take the single.
Tossed up, around off. Kyle Mayers blocks it out.
Floated, on the pads. Kyle Mayers misses his flick and it brushes his pad before going to short fine leg.
Flatter ball, down leg. Jomel Warrican clips it to square leg.

OUT! CAUGHT! That is a terrific running catch from Chamika Karunaratne (sub). Tossed up nicely, around off. Jomel Warrican sees the flight and looks to hoick it but he gets a top edge and the ball loops up in the air over mid off. Chamika Karunaratne (sub) runs there from mid off, keeps his eyes on the ball and completes a really good catch. Ramesh Mendis picks up his sixth wicket and West Indies are bowled out for 253!
Howout: c sub Chamika Karunaratne b Ramesh Mendis

Commentary: Veerasammy Permaul starts with a fuller ball on middle, Dimuth Karunaratne nudges this to the leg side.
Sri Lanka and Dimuth Karunaratne open their account here! Slightly shortish, outside off, punched through covers for a single.
Pathum Nissanka is off the mark straightaway! Flatter this time, outside off, Pathum Nissanka goes back and plays this through point to collect a single.
Around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up, around off, this is pushed back to Veerasammy Permaul again.
On off, fuller, eased through covers and a run is taken. 3 off the opening over!

FOUR! The first boundary in this innings. Fuller, tossed up, outside off, Dimuth Karunaratne leans and strokes this through covers. The fielder in the deep runs to his right and pulls the ball back. They want to check if his foot was in contact with the ropes when he pulled the ball back. Replays confirm that it was and this would be a boundary.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
On off, pushed away to the point region.
Fuller, on off, spins away, Dimuth Karunaratne taps this to point.

OUT! RUN OUT! Dimuth Karunaratne has to depart in just the second over! That was a suicidal attempt to take a run and it proves to be the Lankan skipper's undoing. Great work from Mayers and the Lankans are one wicket down now. Fuller, tossed up, on off, Dimuth Karunaratne pushes this to point and wants a single. Kyle Mayers runs in, collects the ball, and has a shy at the non-striker's end and hits the stumps too. The TV umpire is called in to check and replays show that Dimuth Karunaratne is well short.
Short and around off, kept out.
Full, on off, kept out.
Fuller, on off, pushed to the leg side.
Tossed up, around off, the ball lands and spins away as Oshada Fernando looks to defend and misses.
On off, pushed to covers.
Full on middle, jammed out.
Flatter, on off, punched to point.
Flatter ball, outside off. Pathum Nissanka punches it past mid off and collects a single.
Fuller in length, around middle. Oshada Fernando drills it back to the bowler.
Loopy delivery, around middle. Oshada Fernando plays it with soft hands past mid-wicket for a run. He gets off the mark!
Tossed up, around off, spinning in late. Pathum Nissanka dabs it behind square on the leg side.
Floated, around off. Pathum Nissanka blocks it out.
Flatter ball, outside off. Pathum Nissanka stays back to cut but finds the point fielder.
Tossed up, around middle. Oshada Fernando tucks it to the leg side but it hits Nkrumah Bonner at short leg.
Fuller in length, on off. Oshada Fernando pushes it back to the bowler.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Oshada Fernando works it towards backward point.
Tossed up, around off. Oshada Fernando is solid in his defence.
Floated, on a length, around off. Oshada Fernando blocks it out.
Tossed up, around off. Oshada Fernando defends it to point.
Tossed up, outside off. Pathum Nissanka drives it to cover.
Flatter ball, on off. Pathum Nissanka looks to defend but it goes off the inner half past the short leg fielder for a run.
Tossed up, down leg. Oshada Fernando gets low and paddles it towards fine leg for a single.
Floated, on a length, around off. Pathum Nissanka blocks it out.
Fuller in length, on off. Pathum Nissanka blocks it with ease.
A single to end the over! Tossed up, on a length, outside off. Pathum Nissanka eases it to long off to keep the strike for the next over.
Tossed up, outside off. Pathum Nissanka drives it to the cover fielder.
Floated, around off. Pathum Nissanka blocks it out.
Fuller in length, outside off. Pathum Nissanka drives but Kraigg Brathwaite at cover does well to stop the ball by moving across to his left.
On a length, around middle. Pathum Nissanka defends it out.
Flatter ball, way outside off. Pathum Nissanka cuts it to wide of deep point and collects a couple of runs.
On a length, around off. Pathum Nissanka blocks it out.
Fuller in length, around off. Oshada Fernando eases it to long off for an easy single.
Flatter ball, on off. Pathum Nissanka defends it out.
Dragged down leg. Pathum Nissanka tucks it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Tossed up, around off. Oshada Fernando blocks it to cover.
Floated, around middle. Oshada Fernando looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards square leg.
Fuller in length, around middle. Oshada Fernando presses forward to block it.
Tossed up, on a length, outside off. Pathum Nissanka drives it to long off for a run.
Flatter ball, on off. Oshada Fernando blocks it out.
A bit quicker, outside off. Oshada Fernando lets it be.
An appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved! Fuller in length, darted on the pads. Oshada Fernando looks to nudge it to the leg side but he misses and gets hit low on his pad.
Tossed up, around off. Oshada Fernando defends it off the front foot.
Looped up, around off. Oshada Fernando blocks it out watchfully.
Around off, pushed to long off for one.
On off and middle, kept out.
Loopy, around off, pushed to mid off for a quick single.
Full on off, pushed to covers.
Outside off, fuller, pushed to point.
Outside off, fuller, pushed to sweeper cover for a single.
Loopy, on off, worked to point.
On middle, flicked to the leg side.
Around off, fuller, OF works this through backward square leg for one.
Loopy on middle and leg, played with the turn through square leg for a run.
Full, on off, eased to covers.
On off, kept out.
Loopy on off, blocked.
Short and on leg, Pathum Nissanka misses his flick to the leg side and gets hit on the pad. An appeal but turned down. Too high.
On off, fuller, pushed to short cover.
Fuller, around off, nicely kept out.
Loopy, outside off, Pathum Nissanka stands tall and smacks this one through covers. Roston Chase runs to his left in the deep and stops the ball. Two taken.
Short, on off, blocked.
FOUR! Well played. Flatter, way outside off, Oshada Fernando waits for the ball to arrive and then late cuts this one through backward point for a boundary.
On off, OF defends it very late and dabs it to the off side.
Loopy, around off, Oshada presses forward and blocks.
On off, defended.
FOUR! Second boundary of the over. Shorter in length, outside off again, Oshada Fernando camps back, waits, then slaps this one through point. The ball runs away to the boundary.
Full on off, kept out.
FOUR! Overpitched, outside off, Pathum Nissanka shows the full face of the blade and pushes this through covers. The ball speeds through to the ropes.
This is nudged to the leg side for a single.
On off, blocked.
An action replay of the previous delivery.
Outside off, driven through covers for a run.
Angled into off and middle, Pathum lunges and blocks.
Way outside off, left alone.
Floated, on off, kept out.

OUT! RUN OUT! That's the second run out of the day and Sri Lanka lose another. Miscommunication between both the batters and the hosts are two down here. Shorter, around off, Oshada Fernando taps this one towards backward point. He comes forward looking for a run, Pathum Nissanka responds too, but then sends Oshada Fernando back. The Lankan batter turns and looks to get back, but, by then, Jermaine Blackwood collects the ball and throws it to Joshua Da Silva, who whips the bails off. Replays show that Oshada Fernando is well short of his crease. Sri Lanka behind by 10 runs!
Howout: run out (Jermaine Blackwood / Joshua Da Silva)

Commentary: Outside off, fuller, kept out.
Short, around off, angling in, Charith Asalanka leaves it, as the ball whistles past the off pole to Joshua Da Silva.
Outside off, driven through covers for a run.
Flatter, on off, kept out.
On off, Charith Asalanka gets low and sweeps this to square leg for one.
On middle and leg, kept out to the leg side.
On middle, blocked.
Darted on middle and leg, Pathum Nissanka blocks it out well.
This is pushed back to the bowler.
On off, floated, CA defends it smoothly.
Pitched up, outside off, dabbed to point.
On off, blocked again to the off side.
Fuller again, outside off, Charith Asalanka steps ahead and then makes a leave.
Darted on middle, slightly shorter, Charith Asalanka misses his attempted defense and gets hit high on the pad. An appeal but the umpire says nothing. Would have been too high.
On off, pushed to covers.
Flighted on off, worked to point.
Around off, played to covers.
Nicely flighted, on off, Pathum Nissanka strides ahead and blocks.
Slightly shorter, around off, the ball lands and turns away as Pathum Nissanka goes back and misses his attempted defense.
Shorter again, outside off, punched to sweeper cover for one.
Tossed up, on off, Charith Asalanka sweeps this to deep mid-wicket for one.
Outside off, flatter, Charith Asalanka looks to slash it away but misses.
On middle, knocked to the off side now.
Floated, outside off, turns away as Charith Asalanka shoulders arms.
On off, kept out.
Loopy, outside off, Charith Asalanka is solid in defense.
Charith Asalanka drives this fuller ball to sweeper cover for a single.
Leg bye. Fuller and sliding down the leg side, Charith Asalanka looks to sweep but the ball takes the elbow and goes over the keeper for a leg bye.
On middle, blocked.
Short in length, outside off, slapped to sweeper cover for one.
Flatter, on off, knocked to the leg side.
Too full, outside off, Charith Asalanka gets behind the line of the ball and solidly blocks.
Around off, blocked.
Attacks the stumps with a full ball, kept out.
Outside off, played gently to the off side.
Quicker, shorter, around off, Pathum Nissanka gets his bat down and keeps it out.
On middle, worked to square leg.
Just a touch short around off, Pathum Nissanka goes back and pushes this to the leg side.
Fuller, around off, Pathum Nissanka presses forward and smothers the ball out. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 3!
Chase starts with a shorter ball, around off. Charith Asalanka goes back and pushes it to silly point.
Nicely tossed up, outside off. Bit of turn away from the left-hander so Charith Asalanka leaves it.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, just outside off. Charith Asalanka gets forward and blocks it.
Darted on the pads. Worked to deep square leg for one.
Nicely tossed up, on off. Pathum Nissanka works it towards mid on.
Charith Asalanka comes down the track and taps it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball, on middle and leg. Charith Asalanka sweeps it to short fine leg.
Full and on the pads. Flicked uppishly but wide for short leg for one.
Loopy ball, around off. Pathum Nissanka pushes it to mid off.
Nicely flighted, wide enough to be left alone.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.
Flatter ball, outside off. Pushed away for one.
FOUR! Top-quality shot! Tossed up, outside off. Pathum Nissanka leans into it and drives it to the cover fence.
Pathum Nissanka comes down the track and works it to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball, on middle. Worked past mid-wicket for one.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
A solid defensive stroke to end the over.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, just outside off. Pathum Nissanka gets forward and blocks it.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed to covers.
Full ball, outside off. Driven to deep cover for one.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, on middle and leg. Charith Asalanka sweeps it to fine leg for one.
Floated up, around off and pushed firmly towards silly point.
Slightly fuller, around off, this one goes straight through. Charith Asalanka leaves it alone.
Angled in, around the leg stump. Charith Asalanka looks to keep it out but gets rapped on the pads. A stifled appeal but not given.
On middle, Asalanka keeps it out.
Tossed up, on middle. Asalanka puts out a stride to defend.
Flighted delivery, on the off pole. Asalanka drives it towards cover. Maiden over from Roston Chase.
Flatter one, just outside off. Nissanka rocks back and cuts it towards point.
A touch short and wide, Nissanka cuts it off the back foot but straight to point.
Beaten! Tossed up, around middle. The ball just turns away sharply and bounces a bit extra as well. Nissanka looks to defend but the ball goes agonizingly past the outside edge and the off pole.
Fuller delivery, around off. Nissanka strokes it away to deep point for a couple.
Loopy delivery, on middle and kept out by Nissanka.
Angled in on middle and leg, Nissanka defends it off the front foot.
A touch shorter, around middle and leg. Asalanka goes on the back foot and nudges it towards short mid-wicket for a quick single.
Short and wide, cut away to deep point for a run.
Quicker one, angled in on middle stump. Asalanka pushes it towards cover.
Flatter, around the off stump. Asalanka pushes it back to the bowler.
On off, kept out on the off side.
Nicely flighted, on off. Asalanka defends it out towards silly point.
Pushed through quicker, just outside off. Nissanka keeps it out on the off side.
On a length, around off and defended out by Nissanka.
On middle and defended out with soft hands by Nissanka.
A tad bit short and around off. Nissanka cuts it past short third man and picks up a brace.
Tossed up, on middle. Nissanka strides out to defend.
Tossed up again, on off. Nissanka plays the cover drive but without much timing.
On middle, stroked away towards cover.
Chase drags it down and bowls it around the off pole. Charith Asalanka rocks back and pulls it in front of square on the leg side for a couple of runs.
Slowed up, on off. Asalanka keeps it out on the off side.
On the pads, Asalanka nudges it towards leg slip off the pads and looks for a single. His partner sends him back and rightly so.
Nicely tossed up, around off. Asalanka drives it through cover for a single.
On middle, Nissanka dabs it down towards short leg.
SIX! All the way! This is sheer power. Good use of the feet by Asalanka. Floated, full and on off. Asalanka gets to the pitch of the ball and muscles it over the wide long on fence for a maximum.
A dot now! Tossed up, around off. The ball turns in. Asalanka stays back and defends it out.
Full and on middle. Asalanka gets low and sweeps it to deep square leg and gets a single.
Another single now! Full and on the pads, Nissanka clips it to mid-wicket for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Veerasammy Permaul strikes and gets his first wicket of this innings. A positive start for the visitors. After being hit for a maximum on the first ball, Permaul gets his man after a couple of deliveries and has the last laugh. Floated, outside off. The ball turns in a bit. Asalanka prods and looks to defend it. The ball takes the inside edge onto the pads and it lobs towards short leg. Nkrumah Bonner is placed there who takes the simplest of catches.
Howout: c Nkrumah Bonner b Veerasammy Permaul

Commentary: Dhananjaya de Silva gets greeted by the keeper straighaway. Joshua Da Silva murmurs "Deja vu". Tossed up, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva defends it out watchfully.
Full and on off. NIssanka pushes it towards long off for a single.
Floated, around leg. Dhananjaya de Silva defends it off the pads.
Angled into the pads, fuller, Dhananjaya de Silva looks to defend it out. The ball goes to the off side off the pads.
BEATEN! Some turn and bounce on this one. Full and around off. Dhananjaya de Silva presses forward and loooks to defend it out but gets beaten by the turn.
Flatter, on middle. Dhananjaya de Silva works it to mid-wicket.
On off, de Silva, defends it out watchfully.
Tossed up, full and on off. Nissanka pushes it to cover.
Slower through the air, full and on off. Nissanka defends it with soft hands.
Floated, full and on off. Nissanka pushes it to left of short mid-on.

FOUR! A welcome boundary for the hosts. They will take it however the runs come now. Full and on leg. Nissanka gets low and sweeps it towards fine leg. Roston Chase runs to his right from deep square leg but could not keep the ball in play. Boundary.
On off, Nissanka pushes it out.
Flatter and on off. Nissanka stays back and cuts it towards cover.
Touch short and on off. Dhananjaya de Silva pushes it towards short cover.
Full and on off. Dhananjaya de Silva helps it towards long off for a single.
On the pads, Nissanka stays back and tucks it to square leg for another single.
Tossed up, full and on off. Dhananjaya de Silva takes a step forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
Flatter and on off. Dhananjaya de Silva goes back and defends it to short cover.
Floated, full and on off. Dhananjaya de Silva works it to covers.
Flatter and on off. NIssanka stays back and pushes it to cover.
Full and outside off. Nissanka steps across and defends it out watchfully.
Full and on middle. Nissanka pushes it towards mid on. Permaul chases it down and keeps it down to a single.

FOUR! Nicely played. Dhananjaya de Silva gets his first boundary of the innings. Floated, full and outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva stays back and plays it late. He helps it past the backward point fielder, the ball races away to the fence.

Oh Close! Tossed up, around off. The ball turns away a bit. Dhananjaya de Silva looks to cut it away. The ball takes the outside edge and lobs just in front of the keeper, it does not carry. It was a teaser for the keeper. A tough chance though, but it goes Dhananjaya de Silva's way and not Joshua Da Silva.
Full and on off. Dhananjaya de Silva prods and defends it out solidly.
Nissanka comes down the track and pushes it to short mid off.
Tossed up, outside off. Pathum Nissanka pushes it past cover for one.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, on off. De Silva comes forward and blocks it.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, around off. Dhananjaya de Silva blocks it out to the off side.
Flighted delivery, around off. Pathum Nissanka drives it to short cover.
Flatter ball, on off. Tapped out.
Flighted delivery, just outside off. Nissanka comes forward and blocks it right under his eyes.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed to the off side.
Nicely tossed up, around off. Pathum Nissanka drives it to short cover.
A single as this is pushed down to long off.
Flatter ball, on middle and leg. Nissanka works it past square leg for one.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.
Another solid defense by Dhananjaya de Silva.
Tossed up, on middle. Dhananjaya de Silva sweeps it to deep square leg for one.
Nicely driven to mid off this time.
Loopy ball, on off. Pushed to covers.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Shorter ball, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva goes back and blocks it.

RISKY STROKE! Tossed up, on middle. De Silva gets low to sweep but seems to be in two minds about it. He gets an inside edge which goes onto hit his boot. Had he not hit that, it would have been an LBW.
Flatter ball, around off. Pushed to covers.
Tossed up, on off.  Blocked out.
Flatter ball, wide enough to be left alone.
Shorter ball, around off. Pushed to deep cover for one.
Tossed up, on middle and leg. De Silva dances down the track to block but gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but turned down.
Loopy ball, around off. Pushed past covers for one.
Loopy ball, on off. Pathum pushes it to point.
Tossed up nicely, outside off. Pathum Nissanka drives it to covers but the fielder dives and stops it.
Shorter ball, on off. Worked to the leg side.
Flatter one, outside off, punched away through cover-point for a single.
Slowed up, on a length and around off. Nissanka goes on the back foot and covers the line of the ball well.
Tossed up, on off and defended out by Nissanka.
Flighted delivery, on off. Nissanka defends it right under his eyeline.
Width on offer and Nissanka cuts it away to deep point for a run.
Nicely tossed up, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva caresses it through the cover region for a single.
Tossed up, on off and kept out by Dhananjaya de Silva.
Nicely flighted, around the off stump. Dhananjaya de Silva stays solid in defense.
Slowed up, on off again and watchfully kept out.
On middle and defended back to the bowler.
Tossed up, on middle. Dhananjaya de Silva brings out the cover drive but can't get it through.
Maiden over! Loopy ball, around off and stroked back towards the bowler.

Veerasammy Permaul gives this one some air and bowls it around the leg stump. Pathum Nissanka looks to defend it out but gets hit on the pads. A stifled appeal but not given, probably pitching outside leg.
On a length, around middle and leg. Nissanka defends it off the back foot on the leg side.
Flighted ball, on middle. Nissanka defends it off the front foot.
Looped up, on off and driven nicely through mid off for a single.
Veerasammy Permaul bowls it wider and Dhananjaya de Silva pushes away from his body and gets it towards deep point for a run.
Short ball, well outside off. Pathum Nissanka works it through the point region for another single.
This is pushed through, on middle stump. Nissanka hops back to keep it out on the leg side.
On off, played towards cover.
Tossed up, outside off. Pathum Nissanka drives it with the spin and through cover for a single.
Fullish ball, around leg stump. Dhananjaya de Silva looks to turn it on the leg side but closes the face off the bat early and the ball goes on the off side.
On a length, on off and punched straight to short mid off.
Nicely flighted, around the off stump. Dhananjaya de Silva plays it out on the off side with soft hands.
On a length, outside off. Pathum Nissanka dabs it down towards short third man and picks up a run. He moves to 49 now.
On middle, Dhananjaya de Silva manages to keep it out.

Wide outside off, Dhananjaya de Silva hangs back and guides it nicely through the short third man region. Shai Hope chases this one and manages to pull it back in. The batters comfortably come back for the third and the hundred also comes up for the home team.
On middle, Nissanka defends it out.
Nicely flighted, on off and inviting the batter to drive. Pathum Nissanka steps out of his crease and drives it straight to short cover.
Floated up, on off. Nissanka defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Nicely played. Flatter and on off. Dhananjaya de Silva flicks it through mid-wicket. Jason Holder gives it a chase but the ball wins the race. Boundary.
Looped up, full and on off. Dhananjaya de Silva blocks it out watchfully.
Tossed up, around off. The ball turns away. Dhananjaya de Silva stays inside the crease and plays it towards short cover.
On the pads, Silva tucks it towards fine leg for a single.

Another single now! FIFTY up for Nissanka, his fourth in Test cricket. Flatter and on off. Nissanka stays back and works it towards mid-wicket for a single. A crucial knock by the young man. His team needed this from him.
Full and on off. Dhananjaya de Silva pushes it out for a single. He retains the strike.
A length ball, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva leaves it alone for the keeper.
On a length, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva hangs his bat away from his body and defends it out.
Three dots in a row! A length ball, outside off. The ball nips in a bit after passing the batsman. Dhananjaya de Silva moves across and shoulders his arms.

Three runs now! Back of a length, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva hops and punches it through cover-point. Jermaine Blackwood gives it a good chase and dives in front near the ropes to push the ball back in play. The batters pick three comfortably.
Full-length ball, outside off. Nissanka steps to the pitch of the ball and defends it to covers solidly.
A solid forward defense by Nissanka. A length ball, on off. Nissanka defends it back to the bowler. A tidy over by Roach.
Flighted, full and on leg. Dhananjaya de Silva flicks it to square leg for a single.
Full and on off. Nissanka leans forward and works it towards long on for a run.
Looped up, full and on middle. De Silva tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Full and on off, de Silva comes forward and pushes it towards long on for a single.
Tossed up, around middle. Nissanka defends it to the leg side off the inner half.
Full and on off. Nissanka comes forward and flicks it towards long on for a run. 4 runs coming off it.
Full length, on off. Nissanka comes across and blocks it to cover.
Angled into the batsman. Full, around middle and leg. Nissanka stays back and defends it back to the bowler.
A single now! Back of a length, on the bodyline. Pathum Nissanka hangs back and pulls it towards fine leg. The batters cross for a single.

Nice delivery, a huge appeal by Roach but the umpire is unmoved! A length ball, outside off. The ball nips in off the deck. Dhananjaya de Silva stays back and looks to flick it away. The ball takes the inside edge and hits him on the thighs.
Back of a length, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva drags it pull attempt to mid-wicket.
Full and on the pads. Dhananjaya de Silva nudges it to mid-wicket.
Full and going down leg. Nissanka gets low and sweeps it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Looped up, full and on leg. De Silve flicks it to short leg.
Floated, around middle. The ball turn in. Dhananjaya de Silva looks to defend it to the leg side. The ball takes the top end of the blade and falls in front of him.
On off, Dhananjaya de Silva remains solid in his defense.
Full and going down leg. Dhananjaya de Silva switches his stance and looks to hit it towards fine leg but misses. Joshua Da Silva moves to his left and stops it sharply.
Around off, Dhananjaya de Silva flicks it uppishly towards mid-wicket. They take a single.
Fuller ball, around off. Blocked out.
On a length, just outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva gets forward and blocks it.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out.
On a length, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva blocks it from the crease.
FOUR! Lovely stroke! Short ball, outside off. De Silva rides the bounce and pulls it away. It races to the mid-wicket fence.
FOUR! He does it again! Short ball, on the body. This sits up nicely for Dhananjaya de Silva to swivel and pull. The ball goes to the right of deep square leg for a boundary.
Just short! Loopy ball, on middle and leg. Pathum gets the inside edge which falls just short of short leg.
Darted on the pads. Worked to fine leg for one.
Falls short again! Tossed up, lands outside off and comes back in. De Silva gets the inside edge on the pads but it falls short of the man at short leg.
Flatter ball, on off. De Silva goes back to work it away but gets the inside edge on the pads.
Full ball, on off. Pushed to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Full toss, way outside off. De Silva gets low and sweeps it past square leg for a boundary.
Length ball, on the pads. Pathum Nissanka works it to deep square leg for one.
Length ball, on the pads. Blocked out.
On a length again, around middle and leg. De Silva works it to mid-wicket.
Full ball, on middle. Dhananjaya de Silva blocks it back to the bowler.
Fuller ball, on off. Pushed to covers.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Flatter ball, around off. Nissanka blocks it from the crease.
A single as this is pushed to long off.
Full and on the pads. De Silva gets the inside edge on the pads and past short leg. De Silva wants a single and is down the track but is sent back.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Nicely tossed up, on off. De Silva puts in a nice stride to block it.
Holder starts off with a length ball, down the leg side. Pathum Nissanka looks to flick it away but the ball brushes the pads as Joshua Da Silva dives down to his left to pouch it.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.
Length ball, on the pads. Nissanka works it to deep square leg for one.
Short of a length, on off. Blocked out.
Short ball, down the leg side. Pulled down to fine leg for one.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Full and down the leg side. Nissanka works it to the fine leg fence.
On middle and leg, Dhananjaya de Silva comes down the track to defend it.
FOUR! A half-tracker, around leg stump and punished by Dhananjaya de Silva. He rocks back and pulls it behind square on the leg side and picks up a boundary.
Tossed up, on middle and driven to wide of mid on for a quick single.
Flighted ball, on off. Pathum Nissanka looks to drive straight but gets it off the inner half of the bat towards mid on.
Floated up, on middle and kept out on the leg side.
Good use of the feet from Pathum Nissanka. Tossed up, outside off. Nissanka steps out and strokes it through cover for a single.
On a length, on off. Nissanka defends it off the front foot.
Good-length ball, on off stump. Pathum Nissanka looks to defend it out but gets squared up a bit.
Slightly fuller and angled in on middle stump. Nissanka taps it towards cover.
Length again, around off and angling in. Nissanka stays solid in defense.
This is angled into the pads. Nissanka does well to keep it out.
Maiden over! Short one, down the leg side. Pathum Nissanka looks to pull but in the end decides to let it through to the keeper.
On a length, around off. Dhananjaya de Silva goes on the back foot and taps it past short leg for a single.
Short and wide, Pathum Nissanka is disappointed with that one. It is there to hit and Nissanka cuts it straight cover.
Angled across from round the wicket and Nissanka makes room to stroke it past cover and pick up a couple of runs.
Tossed up, full and on off stump. Nissanka drives it nicely towards long off for a single.
Nicely flighted, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva gets on one knee to sweep it away but gets an inside edge past short leg for a run.

OUT! LBW! Huge wicket just at the stroke of Lunch for West Indies. The change of angle has worked for Roston Chase as he gets rid of Pathum Nissanka, who was looking really good. Tossed up, on a nagging length, around middle and leg. Nissanka goes on the back foot, looking to flick it on the leg side but misses and gets hit on the back leg. The visitors appeal and the umpire raises his finger. The review is taken but there's no bat involved and the ball is clipping top of the leg stump. Pathum Nissanka's fine innings comes to an end.
A gentle fullish ball, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length, around off and angled in. Dhananjaya de Silva dabs it down towards backward square leg where the fielder makes a good stop. They take a single.
A length ball, outside off and stroked away towards cover-point.
An in-dipper this time from Holder, on middle and leg. Dinesh Chandimal pushes it back to the bowler who throws the ball back towards the batter.
Length again, over off stump. Chandimal stays solid in defense.
Good-length ball, around middle and kept out on the leg side by Chandimal.
Angled across from around the wicket, on off stump. Dhananjaya de Silva defends it off the back foot.
Down the leg side and spinning further away, Dhananjaya de Silva shoulders arms.
Short ball, around off stump. Dhananjaya de Silva rocks back and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Nicely bowled. Floated up, around middle and leg. Chandimal is able to block it out.
On middle, nudged out towards cover-point for a quick single. Dinesh Chandimal is off the mark with that as well.
On off and defended off the front foot by Dhananjaya de Silva.
Fullish ball, around off and pushed back towards the bowler.
Very full, on off and Dinesh Chandimal digs it out towards short cover.
Good-length ball, on off and angling in. Dinesh Chandimal gets right behind the line of the ball to block it.
Back of a length, around leg stump and worked past short mid-wicket for a run.
Short ball, around waist height. Dhananjaya de Silva swivels and pulls it towards backward square leg, where Kyle Mayers makes a good stop, keeping it to just a single.
Length again, on top of off stump, Chandimal defends it out with ease.
Floated up, around off and pushed through mid off for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Soft dismissal and Dinesh Chandimal is a goner. Nicely tossed up, on middle stump. Chandimal looks to play the on drive but the bat hits the deck and the ball just lobs up off the face of the bat. The ball goes towards Roston Chase who takes a dolly and is confident that it isn't a bump catch. The umpires go upstairs and the replays clearly show that the ball came off the face of the bat. Dinesh Chandimal looks baffled and Chase is elated. Can the visitors build on this and get rid of the tailenders?
Now some drift on offer! Flighted ball, on off and Mendis gets an inside edge towards short leg.
Tossed up, on middle. Mendis defends it out this time.
Just outside off and played with soft hands towards backward point for a single.

Fifty for Dhananjaya de Silva, a gritty one as well. On a nagging length, around the leg stump. De Silva goes back and forth and gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball rolls onto the off side and they get a single.
A length ball, down the leg side. Dhananjaya de Silva looks to pull it away but the pops up off the thigh pad and Joshua Da Silva with a good take down to his left.
Shorter in length, on middle. Dhananjaya de Silva pulls it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Length again, around middle and nicely tucked away by Ramesh Mendis through square leg for a couple.
On middle and leg, nudged away towards square leg.
Back of a length, on off and slower in pace. Mendis defends it back onto the deck off the back foot.
Holder tries to attack the pads but bowls a low full toss. Mendis manages to get it through mid-wicket and picks up a run.
On off stump, some extra bounce on offer this time. Mendis rocks back to defend.
FOUR! Good shot! Down the leg side, Ramesh Mendis sweeps it behind square on the leg side and picks up a boundary.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Mendis nudges it on the leg side.
On middle and leg, pushed towards short mid on.
Flighted ball, around leg stump and kept out on the leg side by Mendis.
Loopy ball, on leg stump and dipping on the batter. Ramesh Mendis tries to work it on the leg side but gets a leading edge through cover and picks up a brace.

NOT OUT! Really good decision from the onfield umpire because that was really close. Jomel Warrican is right on the money from the get go. Flatter one, on middle and skidding on. Dhananjaya de Silva strides out to defend but gets rapped on the pads. Luckily for him the replay confirms that there was an inside edge and he survives.
Flatter one, on middle nad pushed back to the bowler.
On middle and leg, defended on the on side off the front foot.
Stump to stump from Jomel Warrican. On middle and kept out by Dhananjaya de Silva.
Slightky tossed up, on off and stroked away on the off side.
Fuller one, on off stump and jammed back towards the bowler. Jomel Warrican starts his new spell with a maiden.
Full and on off. Mendis comes forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, on off, Mendis defends it out solidly.
Quicker, on middle. Mendis nudges it to mid-wicket.
Full and on off. Mendis pushes it to long on for a single.
On off, DDS comes forward and works it towards lonhg on for another run.
On off, Mendis is solid in his defense.
Looped up, on middle. Dhananjaya de Silva prods and defends it into the pitch.
Full and on off. Dhananjaya de Silva pushes it to the left of the bowler. Jomel Warrican dives to that side and stops the ball.
BEATEN! Tossed up, around off. The ball grips and turns away. Dhananjaya de Silva gets beaten by the turn here.

BEAUTY! How did it miss the off pole. Looped up, around off. Dhananjaya de Silva stride forward and looks to defend it out but gets beaten by the turn and DDS was left holding his position. The ball sneaks past the outside edge as well as the off pole. De Silva survives this time.
FOUR! Swept away! Full and on leg. De Silva gets low and sweeps it towards deep mid-wicket. The ball goes into the fence.

FOUR! Nice end to the over for the hosts. Two boundaires coming off the last two deliveries. Full and on middle. Dhananjaya de Silva is on the attack now. He gets low and sweeps it through mid-wicket for another boundary.
Full and on off. Mendis works it towards mid on for a single.
Angled into the pads, Dhananjaya de Silva nudges it to mid-wicket for another run. The lead extends to 132 runs now.
Looped up, full and on middle. Mendis defends it to the leg side.
Full and on off. Mendis looks to sweep it away. The ball takes the inside edge, sneaks between the batters leg and goes square on the leg side.
Tossed up, on off. Mendis pats it back to the bowler.
Short and outside off, Mendis cuts it through covers for a single.
Tossed up, around off. Mendis blocks it back to the bowler.
Two dots to start with! On the pads, Mendis stays back and nudges it to square leg.
Flighted, full and on off. Mendis works it to square leg off the inner half. They take a single.
Floated, full and on middle. Dhananjaya de Silva comes forward and blocks it back to the bowler solidly.
Full and on off. De Silva comes forward again and hits it with the toe-end of the bat to the left of the bowler.
On middle. De Silva stays back and punches it back to the bowler. A quiet over by Chase, just a single off it.
Full and on off, Mendis pushes it to mid on for a single.

A mix-up but safe! Flatter and on off. Dhananjaya de Silva pushes it to cover. Mendis is halfway down the pitch looking for a single but was sent back. The fielder collects the ball and throws it to the bowler but the batter was safe inside the crease.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, Silva pushes it towards long off for a single.
Tossed up, on off. Mendis blocks it out watchfully.
A single now! Around middle. Mendis flicks it through mid-wicket for a single. Just 3 runs off it.
Tossed up, on off. Swept to fine leg for one.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, on middle and leg. De Silva blocks it.
Flatter ball, around off. De Silva plays it late and past short third man. The fielder chases it and keeps it to three.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, on off. Ramesh Mendis looks to block but gets hit on the pads.
Flatter ball, on off. Pushed to long off for one.
Fuller ball and pushed back to the bowler.
Shorter ball, on off. Pushed away.
Short ball, on middle and leg. Mendis works it to the leg side.
A single as this is pushed down to long off.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Loopy ball, on off. Mendis gets low and scoops it to fine leg for a couple.
Tossed up, outside off. Left alone.
Full and on the pads. Worked past mid-wicket for one.
Flatter one, around leg stump. Dhananjaya de Silva looks to defend on the leg side but gets an outside edge onto the off side. They take a single as well.
Quicker one, at the pads. Mendis tucks it onto the leg side.
Nicely tossed up, around leg stump. Ramesh Mendis strides out to defend.
Tossed up, on the pads. Dhananjaya de Silva blocks it off the front foot.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out.
Flatter ball, around off. Dhananjaya de Silva is solid in his defence.
Play and a miss! Flatter ball, around off. De Silva looks to punch but the ball turns and goes past the outside edge.
Kept low! Angled on off. It stays as Dhananjaya de Silva goes back to block. But he gets his bat down in time to block it.
Loopy ball, on the pads. De Silva looks to paddle it down to fine leg but gets it on his pads. The man from first slip gets across and stops it.
Darted on the pads. Worked to deep square leg for one.
Tossed up, on leg. Blocked out.
Dhananjaya de Silva blocks this one with soft hands. The ball drops dead near his feet.
Fuller and on the pads. Kept away with ease again.
Darted on middle and leg. Tapped away.
Flatter ball, around off. De Silva looks to run it down to third man but the man at first slip dives and stops the ball.
Quicker and flatter, around middle and leg. Mendis keeps it out on the leg side.
On off and pushed back to the bowler.
Beaten! Tossed up, on middle and the ball grips and turns away sharply, whizzing past the outside edge.
On middle, played onto the leg side.
Tossed up, on off and defended out by Mendis.
Nicely flighted, around off and Mendis strokes it towards cover. Maiden over from Jomel Warrican.
Flatter one, around off. Dhananjaya de Silva defends it out on the off side.

Tossed up, around leg stump. Dhananjaya de Silva plays the reverse sweep behind point and picks up a couple of runs. A short run is signaled though as Dhananjaya de Silva was a bit too eager to get back to the other end.

Huge appeal but not given. Tossed up, around the leg stump. Dhananjaya de Silva looks for the reverse sweep yet again but misses and gets hit on the pads. The umpire shakes his head, probably pitching outside leg.
On middle, DDS comes down the track and eases it towards mid off for a single. The lead is 150 runs now.
On middle and defended out by Mendis.
Nicely flighted, around middle and leg. Ramesh Mendis strides out and works it towards mid-wicket.
Around off stump and kept out on the off side by DDS.
Tossed up, outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva strokes it through the cover region for a run. The 200 is now up for Sri Lanka.
Floated delivery, on middle. Ramesh Mendis defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up, on off and this one turns away. Ramesh Mendis strides out to drive but gets an outside edge past first slip and picks up a brace.
On middle and Mendis stays solid in defense.
Floated it up, around middle and leg. Ramesh Mendis plays it with soft hands on the leg side.
Nicely played again by DDS. On a length, around off. Dhananjaya de Silva makes room and cuts it lately through backward point and picks up a couple.
Tossed up, on off and gently pushed back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter, on off. Dhananjaya de Silva punches it off the back foot through cover and gets yet another brace.
A touch shorter, around leg stump. Dhananjaya de Silva makes room and just about manages to keep it out off the back foot.
Down the leg side, DDS puts out a pad forward but the ball goes straight through to the keeper.
Around leg stump, Dhananjaya de Silva puts out a pad forward again and this time the ball goes off the pads and towards gully.
A gentle full toss, on leg stump. Ramesh Mendis eases it through mid-wicket for a single.
On the pads and nudged down towards short fine leg for another run.
Flighted ball, on leg stump. Mendis defends it on the leg side.
Kraigg Brathwaite gives it some air and bowls it around leg stump. Mendis comes forward and pushes it towards short mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ramesh Mendis falls into the trap and the partnership is finally broken! Nicely tossed up, around middle stump by Kraigg Brathwaite. Ramesh Mendis looks to slog it away on the leg side but he is hitting against the breeze. The slog sweep is mistimed aerially and towards the deep mid-wicket fence. Kemar Roach settles under it and takes a fine catch. Just a lapse in concentration and the skipper, Kraigg Brathwaite has done the job for his team.
Howout: c Kemar Roach b Kraigg Brathwaite

Commentary: Slowed up, on a length and around off stump. Suranga Lakmal looks to slap it away but the ball arrives really later. Lakmal manages to keep it out on the off side.
Tossed up, on the pads. Blocked out.
Down the leg side and Dhananjaya de Silva kicks it away.
Full ball, on off. Pushed to long off for one.
Full ball, on off. Lakmal plays it back to the bowler.
Shorter ball, lands outside off and turns away. Lakmal thinks of cutting it but then leaves it alone.
Flatter ball, on off. Lakmal blocks this and survives.
Flatter ball, around off. Pushed past covers for one.
Full ball, on middle. Lakmal blocks it out.
SIX! High and handsome! Tossed up, on middle and leg. Lakmal comes down the track and heaves it over the long on fence.
Full ball, on the pads. Blocked out.
Just a single as this is pushed past covers.
Full ball, on middle and leg. De Silva gets the inside edge past square leg while looking to block. Single taken.
Full ball, on off. Pushed to covers.
Shorter ball, outside off. De Silva cuts it to deep point for one.
Flatter ball, outside off. Lakmal misses the cut.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.

OUT! LBW! Umpire's call on hitting! Flatter ball, on middle and leg. Lakmal goes back to block but gets hit on the pads. The finger goes up but Lakmal decides this one. There is no bat on it and Ball Tracker shows umpire's call on hitting!
Flatter ball, on off. Mathews gets the inside edge past square leg.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, on off. De Silva blocks it.
Beaten! Loopy ball, lands right on the off pole. De Silva looks to block but the ball turns sharply and goes past the outside edge.
Shorter ball, on off. Pushed to long on for one.
Loopy ball, on middle. Pushed to long on for one.
Loopy ball, on off. De Silva blocks it off the front foot.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out.
Shorter ball, on off. Pushed to covers.

OUT! TAKEN! What a fantastic catch that is! Loopy ball, on off. Mathews is not able to reach the pitch of the ball while looking to block and gets the outside edge. Jermaine Blackwood dives to his right at first slip and takes a sharp low catch.
Howout: c Jermaine Blackwood b Veerasammy Permaul

Commentary: Beaten! Loopy ball, outside off. Lasith Embuldeniya puts in a stride to block but the ball goes straight and beats the outside edge.
Full ball, on off. Blocked out.
Tossed up, around off. Lasith Embuldeniya looks to drive but is beaten.
Tossed up, around leg. De Silva looks to paddle sweep but misses.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Darted on the pads. De Silva looks to paddle sweep again but gets hit on the pads.
Fuller ball, on off. Blocked out.
Darted on the pads. Worked to deep square leg for one.
Loopy ball, on off. Pushed to cover for a quick single.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
SIX! All the way! Tossed up, on middle and leg. Dhananjaya de Silva heaves it over the man at wide long on for a boundary.
Flatter ball, on off. De Silva runs it past first slip. The fielder chases it but they get three.
Loopy ball, on off. Blocked out.
Full and on middle. Lasith Embuldeniya blocks it.
Beaten! Tossed up, outside off. Lasith Embuldeniya looks to drive but is beaten.
Nicely bowled! Drifting into the pads but turns away after pitching, DDS edges it down towards short fine leg.
Fired in at middle and leg, Dhananjaya de Silva nudges it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up, around off. Lasith Embuldeniya taps it on the off side and sets off for a quick single.
Full and straight, pushed back towards the bowler.
Gives it a bit more and air and bowls it around middle and leg. DDS keeps it out on the off side.
Looped up, around leg stump. Dhananjaya de Silva eases it down towards long on for a single and will retain strike for the next over. DDS is now a hit away from his century.
Around off and dabbed down towards first slip where the fielder makes a sharp stop.
Slowed up, on middle stump. Dhananjaya de Silva nudges it on the on side.
Tossed up, on off stump. DDS plays it with soft hands towards short mid-wicket.
On middle, worked around the corner on the leg side for a single.
Quicker one, on a length, just outside off. Lasith Embuldeniya puts out a pad and the ball goes straight to first slip. The visitors think about the review but the ball just wasn't turning enough.
Outside off and padded away by Lasith Embuldeniya.
A rank long-hop, on off stump. Dhananjaya de Silva rocks back and pulls it powerfully towards dep square leg. The fielder from deep mid-wicket is onto it in a flash and keeps it to a single.
Around off and defended out by Lasith Embuldeniya.
On a length, around middle, nudged out on the off side.
Angled in on middle and leg, Lasith Embuldeniya stays solid in defense.
Quicker one, well outside off and left alone by Lasith Embuldeniya.
Around off and Lasith Embuldeniya does well to keep it out and see his team safely through into the Tea break.
Tossed up, around middle and off. Dhananjaya de Silva strides forward and defends it out.
Floated and on off. Dhananjaya de Silva blocks it out watchfully.
Outside off, de Silva guides it towards short third man for a single.
Floated and on off. Lasith Embuldeniya goes back and blocks it watchfully.
Looped up, outside off. Lasith Embuldeniya puts his front leg across and blocks the ball out with the pads. No shot offered this time. A stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
On off, Lasith Embuldeniya remains solid in his defense. He has done his job of surviving the over. Dhananjaya de Silva to take the strike.

Dhananjaya de Silva on 97! Swing and a miss this time! Tossed up, outside off, across the right-hander. Dhananjaya de Silva leans in and looks to push it away but misses. The ball bounces over the blade.
Full and on middle. Dhananjaya de Silva comes forward and plays it back to the bowler.
Floated, full and on off. Dhananjaya de Silva pushes it towards long off for a single.
Looped up, around leg. Lasith Embuldeniya defends it out watchfully.
Looped up, full and on off. Lasith Embuldeniya prods and blocks it out.
Full and outside off. Lasith Embuldeniya defends it out to see off the over.

Floated, full and around off. The ball turns away off the deck. Dhananjaya de Silva looks to defend it out. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to the right of the man at first slip. He dives to that side and collects the ball.

FOUR BYES! Misses everyone! Looped up, around off. The ball turns away. Dhananjaya de Silva looks to push it away but misses. The ball goes between the keeper and the slip fielder and into the fence at third man.

Two runs! Dhananjaya de Silva gets his HUNDRED! A really important knock for Sri Lanka. He put up his hand and took the side to safe shores and has extended the lead to a great margin. Full and on the pads. Dhananjaya de Silva flicks it through mid-wicket and gets a couple.

NOT OUT! Dhananjaya de Silva manages to get back in time. Great work by Nkrumah Bonner at short leg. Full and on leg. Dhananjaya de Silva comes forward and looks to flick it away. The ball ends up with Bonner at short leg, he collects the ball and hits the stumps at the striker's end. The West Indies' players appeal and the umpire takes it upstairs to confirm. The replays show Dhananjaya de Silva had his bat inside the crease.
On off, Dhananjaya de Silva blocks it watchfully.
Full and on off. Dhananjaya de Silva pushes it to cover.
Full and on the pads. Lasith Embuldeniya flicks it through square leg. The batters pick three runs with ease.

FOUR! Dhananjaya de Silva is on the charge now. He wants to keep going and swell the lead. Flatter and outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva goes back and punches it through cover-point. The ball races away to the boundary. 250 up for the hosts now. They lead by 204 runs.
On the pads, nudged to short leg.

SIX! BANG! Full and on off. Dhananjaya de Silva comes down the track and smokes it over the long on fence. It is a risky shot with a man near the ropes. Roach leaps high in the air but the ball eludes him.
On off, Dhananjaya de Silva works it towards mid on.
Flatter and outside off. Dhananjaya de Silva plays it late and cuts it towards backward point for a single.
Full and on off. Dhananjaya de Silva defends it to cover off the outer half. They take one.
Tossed up, full and on off. Lasith Embuldeniya sweeps it through square leg for a single. The runs are coming freely for Sri Lanka at the moment.
Full and on the pads. Dhananjaya de Silva strides forward and blocks it out.
Around off, Dhananjaya de Silva stays back and punches it to long off for a single.
Darted on the pads, Lasith Embuldeniya looks to pull it away but misses. The ball goes off his pads.
Full and outside off. Lasith Embuldeniya looks to push it to the off side but misses. The ball misses the outside edge.
Short and wide, slapped through the cover region for an easy couple.
Around middle and leg, DDS dabs it down onto the deck.
Fuller one, on off and pushed down to long on for a single.
Flatter one, around off. Lasith Embuldeniya keeps it out.
On off, Lasith Embuldeniya steps out and taps it onto the leg side.
Tossed up, around off. Lasith Embuldeniya strides out to defend.
Quicker one, on off stump and cut away straight to point.
Slowed up, on a length and on off. DDS goes on the back foot to defend.
Looped up, on middle and DDS puts out a stride to keep it out.
Nicely bowled. A flatter delivery, on off and going on with the arm. Dhananjaya de Silva gets an inside edge onto the pads.

Difficult chance...put down! Tossed up, on middle. Dhananjaya de Silva goes for the big slog on the leg side but mistimes it badly. The ball goes off the top edge and back over the bowler's head. Veerasammy Permaul runs back and chases the swirling ball but can't get to it even after putting in the dive. They get a single.
On middle and pushed back towards the bowler.
Flatter one, on off and DDS punches it through cover for a single.
Tossed up, around off. Lasith Embuldeniya steps out and pushes it with the turn, down towards long on for one.

Uppish but safe! Flighted ball, around off and turning away. Dhananjaya de Silva looks to cover drive but slices it through point and picks up a couple. The 50 partnership also comes up for these two.
Beaten! Pushed through quicker, on off stump. The ball turns away sharply and there's extra bounce on offer as well. DDS looks to push at it but is well beaten.
Flatter one, on off, kept out with ease this time.
Tossed up, on middle. Dhananjaya de Silva defends it off the inner half of the bat on the leg side.
Quicker one, on middle and Lasith Embuldeniya manages to fend it away.
Full and around off, Lasith Embuldeniya squeezes it out on the off side for a single.
On a length, on middle, pushing the batter on the back foot. Dhananjaya de Silva pushes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, on off and defended off the front foot this time.
Around the off pole and this is stroked through cover for a single.
Flatter delivery, around off. Lasith Embuldeniya nudges it towards backward point.
Back of a length, outside off and tapped straight to point.
A length ball, on the pads. Lasith Embuldeniya flicks it away to fine leg for a single.
Full and wide from around the wicket, Lasith Embuldeniya looks for the booming cover drive but is well beaten.
Fullish ball, around off. Lasith Embuldeniya punches it through cover and picks up a run.
LEG BYE! On a length, around middle and leg and slanting further down. Dhananjaya de Silva looks to flick but this one keeps a bit low and goes off the pads towards fine leg. They take a leg bye.
